message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The skin lesions with a dimpled center suggest the most likely cause is Poxvirus (molluscum contagiosum), especially in patients with HIV infection. Bartonella can cause cat-scratch disease, which does not match the symptoms. Papillomavirus can cause warts, but not with a dimpled center. Coccidioides can cause pulmonary infection, but not skin lesions.
